{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_32","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated `fails-java-run` job failed for `org.fusesource.hawtjni:hawtjni-runtime:1.11`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-4425-fails-java-run-org.fusesource.hawtjni-hawtjni-runtime-1.11-9737f731\n\nThe most likely failing stage is the JVM test run (`:test` inside `:tckTest`). In `human-intervention-logs/org.fusesource.hawtjni:hawtjni-runtime:1.11/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T21-53-11-733745Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/org.fusesource.hawtjni:hawtjni-runtime:1.11/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-02T21-54-01-722030Z.log`, `LibraryTest.loadQueriesClasspathNativeLibraryResourcesWhenSystemLoadFails()` fails because the actual resource lookup sequence contains an extra `META-INF/native/linux64/amd64/libhawtjni_runtime_coverage_probe_missing.so`, while the test still expects only the older 3-path sequence. This is consistent with the 1.11 runtime behavior change: `org.fusesource.hawtjni.runtime.Library#doLoad()` now probes an arch-specific resource path before the platform/OS/generic paths.\n\nNo automated fix was produced. `stats/org.fusesource.hawtjni/hawtjni-runtime/1.11/execution-metrics.json` shows `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `test_file`/`metadata_file` = `None`, so dynamic-access coverage is unavailable for 1.11. After the JVM failure, `human-intervention-logs/org.fusesource.hawtjni:hawtjni-runtime:1.11/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-02T21-54-37-079658Z.log` also records a `MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter` during `runNativeTraceImage`, which may need follow-up once the JVM test is fixed.\n\nManual next steps:\n- Update or regenerate the 1.11 test so it still verifies classpath fallback loading but accepts the additional arch-specific resource probe introduced by `hawtjni-runtime` 1.11.\n- Rerun `./gradlew javaTest -Pcoordinates=org.fusesource.hawtjni:hawtjni-runtime:1.11` and then `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.fusesource.hawtjni:hawtjni-runtime:1.11`.\n- If native tracing still reports `MissingResourceRegistrationError` for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter`, inspect the trace log above and add the needed test-only resource metadata before regenerating stats."}}
